The paper discusses the design-phase safety analysis of vehicle guidance systems, which involves software engineering (cs.SE), robotics (cs.RO), and control systems (cs.SY). The proposed approach also involves model checking, which is a common technique in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) for verifying system properties. Additionally, the paper discusses the evaluation of electronic/electrical (E/E) architectures, which falls under the category of embedded systems (cs.ET).
